HEADWORD: Afferent
<hw>Af"fer*ent</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>afferens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>afferre</ets>; <ets>ad</ets> +
<ets>ferre</ets> to bear.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Bearing or
conducting inwards to a part or organ; -- opposed to
<ant>efferent</ant>; <as>as, <ex>afferent</ex> vessels;
<ex>afferent</ex> nerves, which convey sensations from the external
organs to the brain.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Affettuoso</ent>⟦br⟧
